What each file does
data_level0.bin

This contains the actual vector data (embeddings) and level-0 nodes of the HNSW index.

Think:

chunk_0 → [0.123, -0.456, 0.789, ...]
chunk_1 → [0.111, -0.222, 0.333, ...]

The vectors are primarily stored here.

link_lists.bin

Stores the graph connections between vectors.

Example:

chunk_0 → nearest neighbors:
    chunk_7
    chunk_23
    chunk_55

This is what makes similarity search fast.

header.bin

Stores index metadata:

dimension = 384
vector_count = 154
length.bin

Stores record lengths/offset information used internally.

